A matter of celebration or shame ? Indians are celebrating winning just 1 gold medal in the Tokyo Olympics. India has a population of about 1350 million people. Australia, with a population of 25.8 million has won 17 gold medals. New Zealand with 4.9 million has won 7 South Korea, with 51 million people, has won 6. Kenya with 55 million has won 6. Cuba with 11.3 million has won 6. Jamaica with 2.9 million has won 4. Croatia with 4 million has won 3. Slovenia with 2 million has won 3. Serbia with 6.9 million has won 2 Uganda with 44 million has won 2 Equador with 17 million has won 2 Israel with 8.8 million has won 2 Uzbegistan with 33.6 million has won 2. Qatar with 2.8 million has won 2 Kosovo with 1.9 million has won 3 So is it a matter to celebrate or be ashamed about ?
